content.content: About WoodRiver Energy
Learn More about our team.
Empowering Your Passion®

WoodRiver Energy was started in 2014 with a passion for providing small and medium-sized commercial, industrial, educational, and agricultural customers specialized market solutions to bring savings and manage risk through natural gas transport.

With more than 70 years of combined experience in natural gas, the managing partners recognized that each customer has a unique set of goals and objectives that must be addressed to provide a performance-centered product.

button.buttonText: Learn More About Natural Gas Transport

content.content: Meet Our
Leadership

content.body: Marc is the co-founder and president. With more than 30 years of industry experience, Marc managed Seminole Energy’s marketing business in the Rockies and upper Midwest before starting WoodRiver Energy in 2014.
content.title: Marc Peter
content.subtitle: President

content.content: Our natural gas solutions are built around you

We know that every business is unique and that you have a very specific set of budget needs and goals. That’s why our team will guide you through a range of solutions and help customize a plan to fit your budget.

content.body: VP of Sales, Stacci, has 20 years of experience of marketing natural gas in Nebraska and Iowa. In that time she has developed a wealth of knowledge and experience in the business and the region. With WoodRiver, Stacci is leading the effort to develop WoodRiver’s market position in the region.
content.title: Stacy Urbom
content.subtitle: Vice President

content.body: VP of Business Development, Don, has twenty years of experience in trading and selling natural gas. Most recently he headed up a sales office of 25 people marketing gas in the Rocky Mountain and upper Midwest states. At WoodRiver, Don heads up the company’s business development efforts and supports the company’s on-going sales and marketing efforts.
content.title: Don Krattenmaker
content.subtitle: Vice President

content.content: Our team provides support before, during, and after you enroll
Once you find a plan that fits your needs, let our team handle the rest. We work directly with your utility to handle all the details, saving you time and hassle.

content.body: Starr McNamara comes to WoodRiver Energy with more than 20 years of experience in a variety of senior management roles in disciplines that include finance, accounting, legal, audit, tax, human resources and operations. In her role as CFO to WoodRiver Energy, Starr provides financial leadership to the company, oversees all accounting and administrative aspects, and works closely with the other executive roles to set company strategy.
content.title: Starr McNamara
content.subtitle: CFO

content.body: With 8 years of risk management experience, Michael Ray works to lock in natural gas rate to provide our customers with rate certainty.
content.title: Michael Ray
content.subtitle: Director of Risk and Supply

2021 Agriculture Choice Gas
Natural Gas Programs Built for Agriculture -
Protect Your Profits

No one knows the unpredictability of markets quite like farmers. That why for more than six years, we’ve partnered with farmers to bring budget-certainty to their natural gas through the Black Hills Energy Choice Program.
Natural Gas Programs Built for Agriculture -
Protect Your Profits

No one knows the unpredictability of markets quite like farmers. That why for more than six years, we’ve partnered with farmers to bring budget-certainty to their natural gas through the Black Hills Energy Choice Program.
Our Natural Gas Programs
There isn’t a one-size-fits-all when it comes to your farm. With three natural gas plans and terms up to 36 months, you can choose the best plan that fits your needs and budget.
Guaranteed Index
This plan follows the market price each month. The price can fluctuate depending on weather-driven demand.
Managed Price
This plan brings savings and a level of certainty by locking in 75% of your gas on the Guaranteed Fixed Price Plan and allowing the remaining 25% to follow the market price.
Guaranteed Fixed Price
This plan provides complete budget protection by locking in your price per therm for up to 36 months.
Guaranteed Index
This plan follows the market price each month. The price can fluctuate depending on weather-driven demand.
Managed Price
This plan brings savings and a level of certainty by locking in 75% of your gas on the Guaranteed Fixed Price Plan and allowing the remaining 25% to follow the market price.
Guaranteed Fixed Price
This plan provides complete budget protection by locking in your price per therm for up to 36 months.
Black Hills Energy Choice Natural Gas Program

For nearly 30-years, the deregulation of natural gas has provided the opportunity to purchase natural gas from third-party suppliers in a competitive marketing place. Gas is still delivered through Black Hills Energy’s infrastructure, and they’re responsible for any service or maintenance emergencies. Black Hills Energy is also responsible for mailing your bill. Once you’ve made a selection, you will see the supplier you selected and the rate you enrolled starting June 1, 2021.

Choice Natural Gas Program -
Secure Your Budget

As part of the Black Hills Energy Choice Gas Program in Wyoming and Nebraska, residential and commercial customers have the opportunity to choose a natural gas supplier that offers the best price, service, and program offering to fit their budget and operations.

Frequently Asked Questions

In deregulated markets, gas can be delivered onto the utility system and to commercial customers by third party suppliers such as WoodRiver Energy through a program known as gas transportation. Deregulation and gas transportation have been around since the early 1990’s but only recently has it been viable for smaller commercial customers to participate.
What is gas transport?

Transport allows customers to choose how they purchase their natural gas. Because we work with predictable loads we can efficiently deliver natural gas which in turn allows us to offer you the best rates and services possible. Our products are designed to service specific customer needs including budget certainty or savings. Ultimately, we want to help you find the right solution that best fits your needs.
What are the benefits of gas transport?

Utilities are revenue neutral meaning they cannot make any profit from the purchase and sale of natural gas on behalf of their customers as regulated by public utility commissions. Utilities that have experienced deregulation allow transport because third party suppliers do not alter their revenue stream.
Why do utilities allow transport?
WoodRiver does not replace the utility. Your local utility will still be the ones to call if you smell gas or if you suspect there is a leak.
Does WoodRiver replace utility?

WoodRiver Energy is passionate about our customers. We strive to provide all customers with the best service possible. As a small business ourselves we know what community means and we know how far a personal touch and proactive care goes towards maintaining long standing relationships.
Why choose WoodRiver?

For Your Budget -
Integrated Energy Solutions

You have enough things to worry about; managing your energy shouldn’t be one of them. Since 2014, we’ve helped thousands of business owners to maximize their budget with a customized approach to their natural gas through the local utility’s Natural Gas Transport program.

Now, we’re taking this customized approach to managing your electricity. We’ve teamed up with Shell Energy to provide ConnectedControl, an energy management solution to cut your energy consumption, improve operations, and reduce maintenance costs. All without an upfront capital investment. This integrated approach to managing your energy will save you time, money, and hassle.
